title: Crusaders, Lady Crusaders win at Helias Invitational
text:
Crusaders, Lady Crusaders win at Helias Invitational Sunday, October 11, 2015 Share 
The Helias Crusaders and Lady Crusaders swept the titles in the Helias Cross Country Invitational held Saturday at Jefferson City's Binder Park. 
On the boys side, Helias won the title with a score of 44, beating second-place Russellville by 12 points. 
Elliot Knernschield led the way for the Crusaders by winning the individual title in a time of 16:39.68 on the 5,000-meter race. 
Other top-10 finishers for the Crusaders were Connor Frank in fourth and Brian Kirchoff in ninth. 
The Lady Crusaders rolled to the win by racking up 21 points. Second-place Clinton scored 80. 
Kayla Yanskey of Helias won the individual title, covering the 5,000 meters in 20:06.89. 
Other Helias runners in the top 10 were Abby Hake (second), Kylie Mulholland (sixth), Alli Wieberg (seventh) and Lanie Hentges (eighth). 
Helias finished second in the four-team JV race, four points back of Sedalia Smith-Cottonâ€™s total of 35. Riley Scott was the top finisher for Helias, coming in third (18:57.50). 
Helias was the only team in the JV girls race. Alicia Engelbrecht of the Lady Crusaders won the race (21:10.83).
